er\'s rendering system (`scene.add.text()`, `scene.add.image()`, `scene.tweens.a
dd()`, etc.).\n\nHowever, the design assets in `designs/issue-18/` propose a **R
eact + Tailwind CSS** based UI infrastructure:\n- `import type * as React from \
'react\'` in multiple files\n- `React.Context`, `React.FC`, `React.useId`, `Reac
t.CSSProperties`\n- `clsx` + `tailwind-merge` for class name merging\n- CSS vari
ables via `data-theme` attribute\n- DOM-based accessibility (`aria-*`, `focusWit
houtScrolling`, `ownerDocument`)\n- JSX usage in `usage-example.tsx`\n\nThis is 
completely incompatible with Phaser3\'s Canvas/WebGL rendering pipeline. Phaser3
does not use React, DOM, or CSS for its UI - it renders everything via Canvas/We
bGL.\n\n### 2. PRD Mismatch (BLOCKING)\nPRD-004 (`PRD-004-ui-component-library-r
edesign.md`) explicitly specifies:\n- Phaser3-based components (`Phaser.GameObje
